<p>Edtech's lower growth and higher burn multiples reflect the challenging sales dynamics: school district procurement is slow, budget-constrained, and subject to political influence. The companies that thrive in edtech achieve it through either strong product-led adoption among teachers (bottom-up) or deep relationships with district-level decision-makers (top-down), rarely both simultaneously.</p>
