<p>The improvement trajectory is intentional. As companies mature, investors expect burn efficiency to improve because the cost of acquiring each incremental dollar of ARR should decline as brand awareness grows, sales processes mature, and product-led expansion gains momentum. A Series C company with the same burn multiple as a seed company has not demonstrated the operating leverage that scale should provide.</p>
